~ intro_awaken

Elder: You don't remember me. That is fine. I remember you — all versions of you. This one is the worst so far.
The Tuner: [color=gray](Your frequency is unstable. Fear and instinct are all that remain.)[/color]
Elder: Can you feel the disharmony? It is approaching. 
Elder: Omitus is broken, Ladič. Fragile islands of data in a void of silence.
Elder: I am sending you into the Cathedral of Silence. It is a frozen fragment of the world, trapped in the moment of its collapse.
Elder: Go. Find the Resonance. Tune the world, or be recycled.
- Who are you?
	Elder: I am the Archive. The memory of what was. A consciousness trapped in crystal.
	Elder: Some call me The Elder. You used to call me... something else.
- What am I?
	Elder: A biological shell printed from resonance dust. A fragment of a scientist's soul.
	Elder: You are my tool. My antivirus. But antiviruses aren't supposed to have feelings.
- I'm ready.
	Elder: Good. Disharmony does not wait for readiness.

=> END